CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1775127607
OL,3,CBadenoch won't block Tory coalition
OL,4,Cwith Reform UK in Birmingham
OL,6,FSpeaking in Solihull, Badenoch said
OL,7,Fshe trusts local leaders to make
OL,8,Fdecisions based on their communities,
OL,9,Fwhile reaffirming that the
OL,10,FConservatives will not partner with
OL,11,FReform UK nationally.
OL,13,F"Nationally, we are not going into a
OL,14,Fcoalition with Reform," she said.
OL,16,F"At a local level, it can be very hard
OL,17,Fto form a formal administration.
OL,18,FConservative councillors have
OL,19,Fsometimes had to go into coalitions
OL,20,Fwith the Lib Dems, Labour,
OL,21,Findependents, or other parties.
OL,26,@uD@AOUvD@WO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1775127607
OL,3,CBadenoch won't block Tory coalition
OL,4,Cwith Reform UK in Birmingham
OL,6,F"If they feel Reform is a party that
OL,7,Fwill help deliver Conservative
OL,8,Fpolicies, I will trust the local
OL,9,Fleader to make that decision."
OL,11,FThe comments come ahead of May's local
OL,12,Felections in Birmingham, where Labour
OL,13,Fhas held power for 14 years.
OL,15,FGrowing support for independents and
OL,16,Fsmaller parties could produce a
OL,17,Ffragmented council, potentially
OL,18,Fforcing the Conservatives to rely on
OL,19,Falliances to take control.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@^O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/6
